Good reminder to myself to own things that I am actually bullish on, and not things I am trying to shift on momentum. Some charts look like theyâ€™ll never recover, whereas some things look buyable for the first time in a while. 

When everyone is making hilarious amounts of money I am always tempted to start using leverage again. It is almost impossible to fight the feeling that youâ€™re not making enough, or everyone else is outpacing you. Good reminder that fighting that feeling and avoid the wipeouts is worth it in the end. 

Check on your friends, likely a bad day for many.

Personally, am concentrating my bags into the things I am happy to own for the next few years, and shedding the fat. Realised I own some assets based on not wanting to miss out, rather than on some actual thesis. Days like today are much easier for me if I think my bags will bounce back, and much worse if Iâ€™m losing money owning things I donâ€™t even believe in. 

Donâ€™t let a leverage blowup dictate your long-term views. The future is bright, good things to come, patience is rewarded.
